cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a spiking neural network architecture for motor control of a robotic vehicle, which involves both hardware and algorithm design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on the control of a robotic vehicle, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of sensory feedback and online learning suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, which could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents a proof of concept architecture for motor control, which involves system-level design and control theory, and could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of neuromorphic processors and plastic synaptic weights suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, which could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
